  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Field Engineer(Security Systems)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Overview: </strong>We are seeking a Field Engineer to lead the end-to-end management of security system projects, including CCTV, Intrusion Detection, Access Control, and Audio/Video Intercom systems. You will ensure successful implementation from installation to commissioning, ensuring all projects are delivered on time, within budget, and to the client's satisfaction.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Project Management:</strong> Oversee assigned projects for security system installations, ensuring strict adherence to budget, delivery schedules, and customer requirements.</p></li><li><p><strong>Site Implementation:</strong> Manage the installation, testing, and commissioning phases. Supervise on-site subcontractors to ensure work quality aligns with approved drawings and technical instructions.</p></li><li><p><strong>Stakeholder Coordination:</strong> Liaise effectively with Architects, Consultants, Main Contractors, and Interior Designers to communicate progress, ensure technical compliance, and manage variation claims.</p></li><li><p><strong>Resource Management:</strong> Handle the procurement of materials and coordinate timely site deliveries to support project milestones.</p></li><li><p><strong>Documentation & Handover:</strong> Maintain accurate project documentation, including updating shop drawings, floor plans, and single-line diagrams prior to handover to the Maintenance Department.</p></li><li><p><strong>Customer Engagement:</strong> Conduct comprehensive user training on installed systems. Address customer feedback or complaints promptly by implementing corrective and preventive actions.</p></li><li><p><strong>Reporting:</strong> Attend site meetings and provide regular status reports, forecasts, and technical issue updates to key stakeholders.<br /></p><p>We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates will be\nnotified. Please note that your response to this advertisement will constitute informed consent to the collection, use, and/or disclosure of personal data by EL Connect and, where necessary, to relevant third parties, for purposes such as job applicati processing, career advisory, research, and other administrative\npurposes, in compliance with the relevant provisions of the Privacy Policy.</p><p>Lawrence Pang Swee Yong <br />Registration Number: R1989674 <br />EL Connect Pte Ltd<br />EA Licence No: R2197493</p></li></ul>",
